---
// WhatIs — grounding section between Hero and ProofStrip.
// No cards, no grid. A single centered text block that answers
// "wait, what exactly is Formspec?" before the reader scrolls further.
---

<section class="whatis-section" aria-labelledby="whatis-heading">
  <div class="whatis-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow" aria-hidden="true">What is Formspec</div>
    <h2 class="whatis-title" id="whatis-heading">
      Your form is a file, not a database.<br />
      Your rules are separate from your design.
    </h2>
    <p class="whatis-body">
      A Formspec form is a single JSON file you can open in any text editor, email to a colleague,
      or check into version control. It contains your fields, validation rules, conditional logic,
      calculations, and page flow — everything about what the form <em>does</em>. How the form <em>looks</em>
      is defined separately: a theme controls colors, spacing, and branding; a component document controls
      which interface elements appear. Change the design without touching the rules. Pass an audit on
      the logic, then let your UX team iterate on the interface without re-certification.
      No database. No vendor platform. No coding required.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .whatis-section {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 4.5rem 0;
  }

  .whatis-inner {
    max-width: 44rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .section-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .whatis-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .whatis-body {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
